<TITLE> Mutiny trial in Feni begins </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Feni, Dec 21 (bdnews24.com)Trial of suspected BDR mutineers of Feni region began on Sunday, which is the third in a series of such hearing on the mutiny. Earlier, it took place at Rangamati and Satkhira. At the outset of the trial, a statement of accusation was read out at the special tribunal formed at 19 Rifles Battalion headquarters. Daganbhuiyan police filed a case charging 62 border guards who had expressed solidarity with the bloody rebellion in the Peelkhana headquarters in Dhaka in February. The accused also allegedly fired weapons, with blank shells, and blocked the Feni-Maizdi road on February 26. They were produced before the Feni divisional judicial magistrate's court on May 14, and have been detained in Feni jail since. However, the accused BDR men were not put on the dock Sunday. They will be brought to the court on Monday. BDR director general Major General Moinul Islam led the special court on Sunday afternoon and Lt Col Zaman and Maj Maksud of Comilla sector were there to assist him. The first trial of mutiny suspects began in Rangamati on Nov 24, followed by a trial in Satkhira on Dec 7. The bloody Feb 25-26 mutiny at the border force's Dhaka headquarters killed over 73 people, 57 of them army officers deputed to the paramilitary force. The rebellion also spread to other BDR posts around the country. On Nov 15, the government formed six special courts, including two in Dhaka, to try some 3,500 border guards accused in some 40 cases around the country. b
